Section 1:
Act 574 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/10/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1515
4
5 By: Representatives Painter, Ray
6 By: Senator Crowell
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE AUTHORITY TO
10 ORDER THE ARKANSAS NATIONAL GUARD INTO SERVICE; TO
11 AUTHORIZE THE USE OF THE ARKANSAS NATIONAL GUARD FOR
12 MATTERS RELATED TO MILITARY JUSTICE AND TO ADDRESS
13 STAFFING SHORTAGES; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
14
15
Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE
18 AUTHORITY TO ORDER THE ARKANSAS NATIONAL
19 GUARD INTO SERVICE; AND TO AUTHORIZE THE
20 USE OF THE ARKANSAS NATIONAL GUARD FOR
21 MATTERS RELATED TO MILITARY JUSTICE AND
22 TO ADDRESS STAFFING SHORTAGES.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 12-61-111, concerning ordering the
27 organized militia into service, is amended to add an additional subsection to
28 read as follows:
29 (c) With the approval of the Governor, the Adjutant General shall have
30 power to order into the active service of the state for such a period, to
31 such extent, and in such manner as he or she may deem necessary part of the
32 Arkansas National Guard for:
33 (1) Matters related to the execution of military justice within
34 §§ 12-64-403 — 12-64-405, § 12-64-407, §§ 12-64-409 — 12-64-412, § 12-64-414,
35 § 12-64-504, § 12-64-510, § 12-64-517, § 12-64-606, § 12-64-707, § 12-64-709,
36 and § 12-64-710 for an accused, a witness, prosecution counsel, defense
*ZRC020*
03-10-2025 11:36:03 ZRC020
As Engrossed: H3/10/25 HB1515
1 counsel, a paralegal, a military judge, a preliminary hearing officer, a
2 deposition officer, a marshal, a bailiff, a court reporter, or a panel member
3 when duty status orders under Title 32 of the United States Code are
4 unavailable; or
5 (2) Voluntary support in a state active-duty status of the
6 Arkansas National Guard to address critical staffing shortages related to
7 security and essential military operations.
8
9 /s/Painter
